cards.Name: Swamp Realm
cards.Description: It's alive! This organic track sprouts froma fetid Swamp and winds up around towering trees, growing and branching faster than the cars that race on it.

cards.Name: Canyon Realm
cards.Description: Criss-crossing above an impossibly deep chasm, the Canyon track challenges drivers with sheer drops on every side.

cards.Name: Chrome Realm
cards.Description: Beware: Objects in mirror are closer than they appear! Reality and reflection blur in this Chrome maze where huge silver spheres threaten to crush cars like tin foil.

cards.Name: Fog Realm
cards.Description: A thick Fog hides gigantic obstacles and treacherous switchbacks that twist drivers into each other. No new Shift cards can be equipped to any Vehicle in this realm.

cards.Name: Storm Realm
cards.Description: The Storm track loops and twists around seething thunderheads, forcing racers to slalom through heavy rains and spikes of lightning to escape.

cards.Name: Ice Realm
cards.Description: An unstable plain atop a huge glacier, the Ice track suffers massive geological disruptions - including the impact of falling icicles as huge as skyscrapers:

cards.Name: Wind Realm
cards.Description: A savage vortex of Wind batters racers with REALM car-swallowing tornadoes, furiously swaying tracks and wind-blown debris that flies at supersonic speeds.

cards.Name: Junk Realm
cards.Description: While in this Realm, ANY Mod can be equipped to ANY Vehicle. Modability rules DO NOT apply. Vehicles retain ALL equipped Mods when they advance from this Realm.

cards.Name: Cavern Realm
cards.Description: Glowing geodes and strange fungi light this convoluted underground track, where vicious creatures lie in wait for any metal snacks that happen to drive past.

cards.Name: Solar Realm
cards.Description: Speed is the key to dodging Solar flares: from a sun that blazes beneath the track. So floor it, smear on the SPF 1,000,000 and hope your tires don't melt!

cards.Name: Cliffside Realm
cards.Description: The Cliffside track is perfect for drivers who REALM like hairpin turns, rockslides and waterfalls. And for those who want additional thrills, there's always the giant vulture.

cards.Name: Labirinth Realm
cards.Description: The Labyrinth track's infinite tangle of twists REALM and turns can totally confuse careless drivers... and then its savage Maze Minotaurs will totally trash them.

cards.Name: Metro Realm
cards.Description: The Metro track seems eerily familiar at first, but this ordinary cityscape is devoid of life. Driverless cars and trucks careen along the deserted streets, hunting down racers one collision at a time.

cards.Name: Neon Pipeline Realm
cards.Description: The so-called `Neon Pipeline's` 360 track unnerves most racers because it forces them to drive at all angles - evenupside-down - to complete the course.

cards.Name: Reactor Realm
cards.Description: Don't slow down to dodge the toxic spills throughout the Reactor - dangerous patrol machines are closing in, sweeping the track with laser 'grids' to wipe away anything that moves too slowly.

cards.Name: Ruins Realm
cards.Description: Enormous statues, falling columns and a precarious marble track sprawl through the  Ruins Realm. It's rumored the statues come to life. That would explain the giant fist-prints in all the wrecked cars.

cards.Name: Lava Realm
cards.Description: Ultra-hot driving conditions, flaming boulder super-heated gases and splashing lava pose the greatest threats on the Lava track. Only a cool hand can beat this molten heat.

cards.Name: Cosmic Realm
cards.Description: The Cosmic track consists of energy rings looped around a small moon. Meteors and satellite debris bombard the track and micro-black holes can instantly suck unwary cars to oblivion

cards.Name: Blizzard Realm
cards.Description: The Blizzard track thrusts drivers into a vicious snowstorm with zero visibility, sleet so fierce it punches right through windshields, and snow so deep it buries cars whole.

cards.Name: Cybergrid Realm
cards.Description: A giant, supercharged circuit board, the Cybergrid track is a maze of 90 turns policed by eletronic 'countermeasures' that hunt down cars and burn them to bytes.

cards.Name: Monument Realm
cards.Description: The only way to exit the ancient tombs of the Munument Realm is to decipher their mysterious hieroglyphs - a bit of a challenge when racing past their at 300mph

cards.Name: Desert Realm
cards.Description: On the Desert track, drivers must contend with treacherous quicksand, deadly rock passages and scathing sandstorms. And by the way, those giant scorpions are NOT a mirage.

cards.Name: Warped Realm
cards.Description: In the Warped Realm, normal physics no longer apply: the track twists in on itself like a knot, gravity appears to have gone on vacation, and reality itself gets... well... warped.

cards.Name: Micro Realm
cards.Description: Racing goes miniature on the Micro track where drivers and their vehicles collapse to the size of toy cars and get dropped onto a traffic-filled freeway to compete or be crushed!.

cards.Name: Water Realm
cards.Description: Speeding through race tubes formed of 'solid water', drivers on the Ocean track must contend with hungry aquatic hazards while negotiating an ancient coral reef.
